Metadata: Divarinone, a novel diterpene from the brown alga "Dictyota divaricata" of the Indian Ocean

Brown algae of the genus "Dictyota" contain diterpenes with a broad range of carbon skeletons. A diverse array of structural types, including dolabellanes, dolastanes and a new tricyclic diterpene dictyoxetane, have been isolated from Indian Ocean "Dictyota" species. An Indian Ocean specimen of "Dictyota divaricata" contains divarinone, which is the first example of a new class of diterpene having a novel tricarbocyclic skeleton.
